[[File:Malice McMunn.jpg|right|thumb|220px|Malice McMunn, with her trademark [[Mohawk hairstyle|mohawk]].]] '''Alternative modeling''' is a branch of the [[Model (profession)|modeling]] industry that features models who do not [[Conformity|conform]] to mainstream [[Ideals of Beauty|ideals of beauty.]] Alternative models are often [[niche market|niche]]-specific, with a personal style that represents subcultures like [[goth subculture|goth]], [[Steampunk fashion|steampunk]], and [[fetishism]]. An alternative model may, for example, be [[tattoo]]ed, [[Body piercings|pierced]], or have other [[body modification]]s, have distinctively subcultural hair such as being [[Shaved head|shaved]], dyed a distinctively unnatural color, or styled into a [[Mohawk hairstyle|mohawk]] or [[dreadlocks]]. Alternative modeling can be clothed or [[Nude (art)|unclothed]].
Alternative modeling was given substantial mainstream media coverage in the last decade, partly through the creation and popularization of community-based alternative modeling paysites, like [[GodsGirls]] and [[SuicideGirls]]. Alternative modeling community sites usually promote their models for their personality as well as for their looks and portfolio.
Examples of alternative models are Jéssica Veneno from Brasil and Dany Divine from London.
==Markets== Alternative models are often employed to promote niche products, either in shops or online, particular subcultural clothing shops and websites.
