[[Image:Stallis 1.jpg|thumb|275px|Stallmästaregården in 2007.]]

'''Stallmästaregården''' (or '''Stallmästargården''') is a historic [[Public_house#Inns|inn]] adjacent to the [[Hagaparken|park around the Royal Pavilion at Haga]] in [[Solna Municipality|Solna]], just north of the [[Stockholm]] city limits. It has existed since the 17th century, and is mentioned numerous times in the works of [[August Strindberg]].<ref>[http://runeberg.org/strindbg/tjanson1/0266.html Samlade skrifter av August Strindberg / 18. Tjänstekvinnans son. Del 1 / 266].</ref><ref>[http://runeberg.org/strindbg/giftas/0008.html Samlade skrifter av August Strindberg / 14. Giftas / 8].</ref><ref>[http://runeberg.org/strindbg/gotiska/0013.html Samlade skrifter av August Strindberg / 40. Götiska rummen / 13].</ref>

